<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Batter up! The first baseball game released for the PlayStation, Bases Loaded 96: Double Header offers a full MLBPA license with 700 players, statistics, and ratings based on the 1994 season, three modes of play including season, exhibition, and championship, one-for-one trades and your choice of seven big league stadiums (plus a special Jaleco park). 
			      <br><br>Options include errors, the DH rule, wind, and automatic fielding. As you embark on your season (which can be adjusted to 13, 26, 52, or 162 games), you'll need to adjust your lineup and set your pitching rotation to achieve the perfect balance. Season progress can also be saved to a memory card with six blocks free. Can you take your team to the championship?
			      <br><br>Slide head first into the ultimate baseball simulation for the next generation. 
			      <br><br>Features: 
			      <br>- Hyper-realistic 3-D rendered excitement
			      <br>- Exhibition variable season and championship play
			      <br>- Complete statistical tracking
			      <br>- Trade deadline-updated 1995 team rosters.
			      <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>The Newest Edition of the Bases Loaded Signature Series
			      <br><br>SLAM your way through 162 games of hard hitting baseball action! Go head-to-head in an exhibition match, or run for the Championship; all in beautifully rendered major league ballparks. With the statistical tracking of 700 MLBPA licensed stars, analyze your player performances throughout the entire season or during a single game. All the spectacle and glory of the perfect season is in your hands!
			      <br><br>Exhibition, Variable Season, and Championship modes.
			      <br>Complete statistical tracking
			      <br>Trade deadline updated 1995 team rosters.
			      <br>Statistics and Ratings provided by STATS, Inc.
			      <br>Huge photos of MLBPA licensed players.
			      <br>Seven stadiums plus one bonus ballpark.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>3D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Baseball theme.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

